column2: Clear bright sunny day- calm lake surface. Temperature and D.O. profile obtained with Hydrolab MiniSonde 4a generously loaned by Dr. James Cotner- Department of Ecology- Evolution- and Behavior- University of Minnesota.   Data entered for 08/10/2007 for readings from surface to 8.34 meters.  Data for rest of profile (8.8 to 16.04 meters) were entered for date of 08/11/2007 due to lack of reporting space for 08/10/2007.
Secchi disk training session with Dave Blumer and Frank Barnwell.  Calm- sunny day.

column1: Made quick survey of lake for invasive Eurasian Water-milfoil- Curly-leaf Pondweed- and Purple Loosestrife and found no signs of any.

column2: Warm- sunny and breezy.  Beautiful day

column1: One young loon present  also 2 gray heron

column2: 60 degrees-  7 Swans on the lake very noisy- all 4 lake monitors on board- 3 boys fishing
Observed otter swimming alone-Partly sunny- slight breeze about 65 degrees 2 loons don't appear to be nesting   1 fisherman-no fish yet
Bright Sunny -  June Bloom water is full of green specks-  one loon-no one else on lake
Bright Sun- one loon on  lake- slight breeze
Bright sun- 2 loons- cloudless sky- Beautiful day.  68 degrees
Hot day- 87 degrees- 2 loons on lake-  sometimes as many as six for short periods- slight breeze
Beautiful- breezy.  loons are gone and leaves are turning

column1: Saw two banded swans on the 15th

column2: Clear beautiful sky- frost last night 55 degrees today.  Slight breeze Water low
Cool green algae globs in water- no breeze-need rain-Loons lost eggs to (beaver)  Heron on lake
Hot- sunny--no breeze   need rain  Loons here Water lever very low-
Sunny-  75 degrees- feels like fall-  Slight breeze-  Loons have left-  Saw 6 herons on lake- level still very
Overcast and very warm 82 degrees-lake still very low-but is clearer in appearance-still seeing

column1: ducks- herons and beaver swam by Dave and Leah's dock-
Wind slight out of the NW
We are only ones of the lake- just a wonderful spring day- leaves just starting to show
Good day to be on the water

column2: Sunny- slight breeze out of NE  Only one loon  Daughter Julia home from France
Clear with few clouds-  very light breeze no one on the lake but us.   Very beautiful day   First day

column1: of trying to take a chemical test.   What an experience. NO Loon   we have seen only one from time
to time.  Think it might be because we have and 4  (four) eagles flying around.

column2: Clear cloudless sky.  Beautiful blue/like Montana Blue  No wind 65 degrees
High clouds-filtered sun- choppy on lake- breezy.  Beautiful fall day-  Yesterday it was over 80 degrees today looking

column1: at high 60's.  Some boaters fishing- not much action- kayaking was great.  Will do chemical testing tomorrow  No loons and humming birds are starting to leave. Lots of deer   No Bear action lately
